+# Engineering Workshop Contract and Reference Bridge V1
+
+Mission: `ENG-20260723-035939-D25D23`
+
+This add-only foundation installs a shared machine-readable contract layer for the
+Engineering Workshop and future Agent Fox Technical Core work.
+
+## What it fixes
+
+- Exact Workshop plan fields are validated before a package is delivered.
+- `replace_text` requires `old` and `new`; `old_text` and `new_text` fail clearly.
+- Package ZIP and extracted-folder roots are checked before preview.
+- Real Python source symbols and helper signatures can be exported with hashes.
+- Proposed patches can be applied to a temporary copy of the actual source.
+- Workshop receipt failures can be reduced to the exact failing validation and traceback.
+- Small mission-specific reference capsules can be uploaded instead of manually pasting
+  long source files and receipts.
+
+## Installed commands
+
+Use:
+
+```bat
+RUN_CONTRACT_BRIDGE.bat validate-plan "Z:\FOXAI\PACKAGE\PLAN.json"
+RUN_CONTRACT_BRIDGE.bat inspect-current --project-root "Z:\FOXAI"
+RUN_CONTRACT_BRIDGE.bat check-folder "Z:\FOXAI\PACKAGE" --expected-name "PACKAGE"
+RUN_CONTRACT_BRIDGE.bat explain-receipt "Z:\FOXAI\System\EngineeringWorkshop\receipts\...\receipt.json"
+RUN_REFERENCE_REFRESH.bat
+```
+
+The refresh command is explicit. There is no background scan or monitoring.
+
+## Safety boundary
+
+The bridge uses fixed files or an explicit caller-supplied file list. It does not walk the
+filesystem, use the network, install packages, inspect live processes/services/listeners,
+measure live resources, call a model, launch a GUI, diagnose, repair, optimize, recommend
+system changes, or access `K:`.
+
+The existing Workshop parser, executor, shared Agent Fox adapter, Desktop, WebUI, V1B-3A
+broker, V1B-2 provider, and frozen Technical Core manifest/guide are unchanged.
